Here is the complete catalog of every Result/Either/error-as-value pattern found across the codebase.

---

## Pattern Examples: Result-Type and Error-As-Value Patterns

---

### Pattern 1: Custom `Result<T, E>` type — `{ ok: true; value: T } | { ok: false; error: E }`

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/core/ai-sdk/src/core/server/result.ts`
**Used for**: AI SDK runtime — session validation, message processing

The type and all combinators are defined here:

```ts
export type Result<T, E = Error> =
  | { ok: true; value: T }
  | { ok: false; error: E };

export const Ok = <T>(value: T): Result<T, never> => ({ ok: true, value });
export const Err = <E>(error: E): Result<never, E> => ({ ok: false, error });

export function mapResult<T, U, E>(result: Result<T, E>, fn: (value: T) => U): Result<U, E>
export function andThen<T, U, E>(result: Result<T, E>, fn: (value: T) => Result<U, E>): Result<U, E>
export function mapError<T, E, F>(result: Result<T, E>, fn: (error: E) => F): Result<T, F>
export function unwrapOr<T, E>(result: Result<T, E>, defaultValue: T): T
export function allOk<T, E>(results: Result<T, E>[]): results is { ok: true; value: T }[]
export function collect<T, E>(results: Result<T, E>[]): Result<T[], E>
```

**Consumed in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/core/ai-sdk/src/core/server/runtime.ts:31-32`

```ts
import type { Result } from "./result";
import { Err, Ok } from "./result";

export async function validateSession(...): Promise<Result<ValidatedSession, ApiError>> {
  // ...
  return Ok({ exists: false });
  return Err(new SessionForbiddenError());
}

export async function processMessage(...): Promise<Result<ProcessMessagesResult<TMessage>, ApiError>> {
  // ...
  return Err(new NoUserMessageError());
  return Ok({ allMessages, recentUserMessage: message });
}
```

**Test coverage**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/core/ai-sdk/src/core/server/result.test.ts` — full coverage of `Ok`, `Err`, `mapResult`, `andThen`, `mapError`, `unwrapOr`, `collect`, and async `Result` composition.

---

### Pattern 2: `neverthrow` library — `Result<T, E>` with `.match()`

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/packages/app-config/src/parse.ts`
**Installed in**: `packages/app-config/package.json` — `"neverthrow": "catalog:"` (catalog version `^8.2.0` in `pnpm-workspace.yaml:47`)

```ts
import type { Result } from "neverthrow";
import { err, ok } from "neverthrow";

export async function loadConfig(repoPath: string): Promise<Result<LightfastConfig, ConfigError>> {
  // ...
  return err(new ConfigError(`...`, "FILE_NOT_FOUND", error));
  return err(new ConfigError(`...`, "INVALID_YAML", error));
  return ok(parseResult.data);
}

export function validateConfig(config: unknown): Result<LightfastConfig, ConfigError> {
  const parseResult = LightfastConfigSchema.safeParse(config);
  if (!parseResult.success) {
    return err(new ConfigError(`...`, "VALIDATION_ERROR", zodError));
  }
  return ok(parseResult.data);
}
```

**Usage example from the JSDoc**:
```ts
result.match(
  (config) => console.log("Loaded config:", config),
  (error) => console.error("Failed to load config:", error.message)
);
```

`neverthrow` is **only a dependency of `@repo/app-config`** — it is not installed globally across the monorepo.

---

### Pattern 3: `{ ok: true; ... } | { ok: false; error: string }` — inline discriminated unions (no shared type)

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/platform/src/lib/oauth/authorize.ts:45-47`
**Used for**: OAuth URL building

```ts
type AuthorizeResult =
  | { ok: true; url: string; state: string }
  | { ok: false; error: string };

export async function buildAuthorizeUrl(params): Promise<AuthorizeResult> {
  // ...
  return { ok: false, error: "unknown_provider" };
  return { ok: false, error: "invalid_redirect_to" };
  return { ok: true, url, state };
}
```

---

### Pattern 4: `{ success: true; ... } | { success: false; error: string }` — discriminated union with `success` key

**Found in 4 separate locations:**

**4a. Named interface pairs** — `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(api)/lib/with-api-key-auth.ts:23-37`

```ts
export interface AuthSuccess {
  auth: ApiKeyAuthContext;
  success: true;
}
export interface AuthError {
  error: { code: string; message: string };
  status: number;
  success: false;
}
export type AuthResult = AuthSuccess | AuthError;
```

Same pattern mirrored in `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(api)/lib/with-dual-auth.ts:22-36` with `DualAuthSuccess`, `DualAuthError`, `DualAuthResult`.

**4b. Inline return type** — `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/app/src/lib/activity.ts:112-115`

```ts
export async function recordCriticalActivity(
  data: ActivityData
): Promise<
  { success: true; activityId: number } | { success: false; error: string }
> {
  // ...
  return { success: false, error: `Invalid activity data: ...` };
  return { success: true, activityId: result?.id ?? 0 };
  return { success: false, error: parseError(error) };
}
```

A second function at line 212: `Promise<{ success: true } | { success: false; error: string }>`.

**4c. Local `ValidationResult<T>` interface** — `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/packages/app-providers/src/runtime/validation.ts:4-8`

```ts
interface ValidationResult<T> {
  data?: T;
  errors?: string[];
  success: boolean;
}
// wraps Zod safeParse output
return { success: true, data: result.data };
return { success: false, errors: [...] };
```

---

### Pattern 5: `kind`-discriminated union (not `ok`/`success`)

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/platform/src/lib/oauth/callback.ts:44-48`
**Used for**: OAuth callback result routing to Next.js route handler

```ts
export type CallbackProcessResult =
  | { kind: "redirect"; url: string }
  | { kind: "inline_html"; html: string; status?: number }
  | { kind: "error"; error: string; status: number };
```

---

### Pattern 6: `storeOAuthResult` — does NOT use a Result type

**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/api/platform/src/lib/oauth/state.ts:82-113`

`storeOAuthResult` returns `Promise<void>`. The "result" in its name refers to the OAuth flow outcome (a Redis-stored status payload), not an error-as-value pattern.

```ts
export interface OAuthResultData {
  error?: string;
  provider?: string;
  status: "completed" | "failed";
}
export async function storeOAuthResult(state: string, data: OAuthResultData): Promise<void>
```

---

### Pattern 7: Custom error classes (`extends Error`)

All six locations:

| Class | File | Fields |
|---|---|---|
| `DomainError` | `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/packages/lib/src/errors.ts` | `code`, `status`, `requestId`, `cause`, `metadata` |
| `ApiError` (abstract) + 15 subclasses | `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/core/ai-sdk/src/core/server/errors.ts` | `statusCode`, `errorCode`, `category`, `severity`, `source`, `metadata` |
| `ConfigError` | `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/packages/app-config/src/parse.ts` | `code: "FILE_NOT_FOUND" \| "INVALID_YAML" \| "VALIDATION_ERROR" \| "READ_ERROR"` |
| `PineconeError` + 4 subclasses | `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/vendor/pinecone/src/errors.ts` | `code`, `cause` |
| `EncryptionError` / `DecryptionError` | `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/packages/lib/src/encryption.ts` | `cause` |

`ApiError` helpers: `toApiError`, `toMemoryApiError`, `toAgentApiError`, `isApiError` all live in `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/core/ai-sdk/src/core/server/errors.ts`.

---

### Pattern 8: Zod `safeParse` — direct usage (not wrapped)

Used across 11 files. Two representative patterns:

**Inline branch** — `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/app/src/app/(auth)/_actions/sign-in.ts:12`
```ts
const parsed = emailSchema.safeParse({ email: formData.get("email") });
if (!parsed.success) {
  redirect(serializeSignInParams("/sign-in", { error: message }));
}
```

**Route handler guard** — `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/platform/src/app/api/ingest/[provider]/route.ts:102`
```ts
const headersParsed = webhookDef.headersSchema.safeParse(headersObj);
if (!headersParsed.success) {
  return Response.json({ error: "missing_headers", issues: headersParsed.error.issues }, { status: 400 });
}
```

